u informed as I progress along.

In about a month we shall leave Cambridge for the summer, though I do not know yet our exact itinerary. My permanent address will remain "Prof. V. Nabokov, Goldwin Smith Hall, Cornell University, Ithaca, N.Y.".

One more thing I would like to mention. The Chekhov Publishing House of the Ford Foundation has just published my novel "DAR" ("The Gift"). This book deals with the development of a writer of genius. It contains his early poetry, the material he assembles